The paper deals with scheduling tasks and analyzing the space needed by the processor to store active tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. However, the paper also deals with stochastic task generation and tail bounds, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Theory (cs.IT), or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Given that the paper focuses more on the scheduling aspect and the analysis of space requirements, we believe that cs.DS is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SY, and cs.AI.
